text: Jaouad Syoud (born 17 September 1999) is an Algerian swimmer. == Career == He competed in the 2018 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m). He also represented Algeria at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships in the 200 metre individual medley and 400 metre individual medley events. He also competed in swimming at the 2019 African Games.
